main event: Two orange objects, resembling basketballs, were observed flying at varying altitudes in California.
interesting points: Objects were thought to be afterburners from jets,One object was seen passing at 10,000 ft and another at 6,000 ft,The sighting lasted approximately 30 seconds,The observer was a military pilot,The observation took place during an overcast morning.
sighted object: two orange objects in the sky
location: 170 miles SW of Santa Rosa Island, California, USA
witness description: military pilot, 2nd Lt Leland N Martin
